  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nI noticed that CI is not surfacing certain linting issues. For example, [this CI run had a linting warning](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/runs/4435405432?check_suite_focus=true#step:8:546) but completed successfully. I think these sort of warnings should be treated as errors since we inevitably have to go back and fix the linting issues eventually anyway. Might as well catch the problems up front.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nCI linting warnings like the one linked above should be treated as errors so that we can catch issues up front.\r\n\r\n",
